race.comment: TORPEDOES (7) has progressed the right way in his past two and looks to be hitting peak fitness now. The blinkers going on should really switch him on, and if he finds the front, he'll be very hard to reel in. CATHAY EXPRESS (10) made strong late inroads at Murray Bridge after spotting them a big start. The rise in trip suits perfectly, though he'll likely drift back again from the draw and be produced late. PRETTY PERKY (11) her run here two back is right up to the mark. Opperman's booking from a soft draw is a positive, and she's capable of bouncing back. BELONGTOJILL (8) was narrowly denied fresh before a flatter effort last start, but third-up she can rebound. Worth including in the minors.
